parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and potentially result in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly accelerates without warning
especially when making a sudden stop
or when the engine is cold or humid.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unstable acceleration can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and potentially result in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle pulls to one side
especially when accelerating in lower gears or giving more than half throttle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Tire failure can lead to loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries, especially at high speeds.
The sudden shattering or blowing off of the sun roof can cause a loud noise, distraction, and debris on the road, increasing the risk of accidents and potentially causing injuries to occupants.
symptoms: The sun roof cracks into hundreds of tiny blemishes
the sun roof blows off the vehicle while driving.
